    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-14T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="796"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d796">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1446</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Special Agent at Corfu</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DHP1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodge</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="2" xml:id="d796fn2">Substance repeated, by telegram No.
                        6891 of the same date, to the Ambassador in Great Britain.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-14T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>This Government would have no objection to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PNP1"
                        >Pashitch</persName>’s stating in Parliament, if necessary, that the
                    speeches of the President did not describe detailed program of war aims but only
                    briefly summarized <pb facs="0886" n="794" xml:id="pg_794"/> them. The
                    Government of the United States would furthermore have no objections on its part
                    to his declaring that if Servia’s allies won the war they would meet Serbo-Croat
                    national aspirations as far as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
